calculated from their spectroscopic\nredshift, are very similar. It is found that the dilution factors of the two\nrelativistic SN IcBL are very different to those of the GRB-SNe, meaning that\nthese engine-driven events may arise from fundamentally different progenitor\nsystems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 May 2018 10:01:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-18"}
